		<fdd:description>QuickTime file format that wraps an Apple video bitstream with other data chunks, e.g., audio.  Apple video encoding is part of QuickTime production software.</fdd:description>
		<fdd:shortDescription>QuickTime wrapper with Apple video bitstream and other data chunks, e.g., audio. Apple video encoding is part of QuickTime production software.</fdd:shortDescription>
		<fdd:productionPhase>Used as a final-state format for enduser delivery; may also be used as a middle-state format, e.g., as the video source when producing lower-resolution streaming versions. </fdd:productionPhase>
